<br>
When playing one of my high level chars I can easily afford 30pp for a port, when on a level 20-30 char I cant afford that much. The donation system works for everyone IMO. It allows the porter to make extra cash from those who can afford it, while still offering services to those who can't. It's a win/win for everyone. I can't imagine what the problem is?<br>
<br>
I never think of a person who shouts "services for donations" as greedy, and I've never had one complain that I didnt give enough, even if I only offered a few plat while playing an alt.<br>
<br>
Of course that's just me. I wouldn't ever attend a church that suggested I pay them a percentage of my annual income to the church, but I have no problem with the hat passing where you give what you feel you can afford. Same thing with charities. If they've set the amount that I have to give, they get nothing (excluding purchasing an item for charity, where the set price is understandable).<br>
<br>
I've always thought that the "services for donations" was one of the more charming aspect of EQ society and a system that works all the way around. <br>
<br>
This is a real clear example of never being able to please all of the people, no matter what you do. <p><hr><img src="http://server38.hypermart.net/danii1/Saip2.jpg"><br><b>Saippenu</b><br>Cleric of 50 Ages<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uvenen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Venen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Whore</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/2/01 11:49:52 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.crocker.com/~denise/amflag.gif  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ranting for Donations</span><hr size=1> Donating is an act of good will, inspired by good will and carried out by good will.  You aren't donating if it isn't for a cause other than yourself.  That is paying.  If you give a little extra, that would be called a tip.  It's more of a grammar issue than anything else, I don't consider them greedy but I think too many have watched others and just carried on the tradition without giving a second thought. <p><img src="http://venen.homestead.com/files/venzsig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ullorianlanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llorian Lanys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Whore</span><br> <font color=#000033>(12/2/01 12:01:43 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.mindspring.com/~suretang/images/usf2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ranting for Donations</span><hr size=1> /agree venen<br>
<br>
A required &quot; donation &quot; is not a donation, it is a &quot; FEE &quot;.<br>
<br>
Its more a matter of sematics actually.<br>
<br>
I never minded :<br>
<br>
&quot; porting /sowing / casting clarity at the gate, Donations accepted but not required &quot;.<br>
<br>
<br>
or something of that nature.  That tells people you are looking for donations if they can afford it, but are not REQUIRING them.<br>
<br>
&quot; porting for donations &quot; says  &quot; i will not port you unless you donate. &quot;  At least it does to me, and to many , many other people.<br>
<br>
When i was a young shaman, i used to say &quot; sowing / binding at gate, donations gladly accepted but not required &quot;.  And i would get anything from nothing to 10 plat.  This was back in january of 2000, when the server was fairly new.  It was a decent way to pay for spells and i dont mind people making money from them.<br>
<br>
When i was playing and on my enchanter, if someone said &quot; porting to XXX donations accepted but not required &quot;, if i needed a port and sent them a tell, i normally gave them between 30 and 60plat, depending on where they were porting me.<br>
<br>
&quot; porting for donations &quot; always got the standard 10pp for a port.  <br>
<br>
Mabye thats just me.<br>
